# UI Component Conventions

## Button

Always import from `@/components/ui/button`. It supports shadcn/ui standard props:

- **`asChild`** — render as `<Link>` or `<a>` while keeping button styling:
  ```tsx
  <Button asChild>
    <Link href="/page">Go</Link>
  </Button>
  ```
- **Sizes**: `xs`, `sm`, `default`, `lg`, `icon`, `icon-xs`, `icon-sm`, `icon-lg`
- **Variants**: `default`, `destructive`, `outline`, `secondary`, `ghost`, `link`

## Three-stage responsive buttons (icon / text / icon+text)

All action buttons in tables and toolbars must use this pattern:

```tsx
<Button size="sm" variant="secondary">
  <Pencil className="h-4 w-4 sm:hidden lg:inline" />
  <span className="hidden sm:inline">Edit</span>
</Button>
```

| Screen | Shows | How |
|--------|-------|-----|
| Mobile (<640px) | Icon only | icon visible by default, text `hidden` |
| Tablet (640–1023px) | Text only | icon `sm:hidden`, text `sm:inline` |
| Desktop (≥1024px) | Icon + text | icon `lg:inline`, text `sm:inline` |

## SlideDrawer

Use `<SlideDrawer>` from `@/components/ui/slide-drawer` for all slide-over panels. Never implement inline translate-x drawers.

```tsx
<SlideDrawer open={open} onClose={() => setOpen(false)} title="Details" side="left">
  <div className="overflow-y-auto p-3">{content}</div>
</SlideDrawer>
```

Props: `side` ("left" | "right"), `widthClass`, `zClass`, `passthrough` (for stacked drawers).

## Shared form types

Import from `@/lib/types/form.ts` — never define locally:
`InputType`, `SelectOption`, `BooleanBranchChild`, `ShowWhenRule`, `SelectChild`, `RepeatableFieldConfig`, `RepeatableConfig`

## Shared utilities

- Date formatting: import from `@/lib/format/date`
- Formula evaluation: import from `@/lib/formula`
- Server-side fetch with cookies: import `serverFetch` from `@/lib/auth/server-fetch`
- Column presence checks: import `getPolicyColumns` from `@/lib/db/column-check`
